1
00:00:08,475 --> 00:00:12,112
Being your teacher
was just my temporary form.

2
00:00:15,415 --> 00:00:18,451
I am going back to my own world.

3
00:00:18,952 --> 00:00:22,055
And where is that?

4
00:00:27,093 --> 00:00:28,995
Far beyond the moon.

5
00:00:29,863 --> 00:00:31,798
Nebula M78.

6
00:00:32,365 --> 00:00:33,933
Near Iscandar.

7
00:00:39,672 --> 00:00:41,207
I'm sorry, but…

8
00:00:41,741 --> 00:00:44,477
I will erase all your memories of me.

9
00:01:02,729 --> 00:01:03,897
Goodbye.

10
00:02:40,860 --> 00:02:43,997
Here he comes!

11
00:02:48,001 --> 00:02:50,270
I have won the Chairman’s Award!

12
00:02:50,336 --> 00:02:51,604
CHAIRMAN'S AWARD - TAZAWA TRADING

13
00:02:54,807 --> 00:02:56,242
SALES DEPARTMENT

14
00:02:56,309 --> 00:02:57,710
Settle down.

15
00:02:58,611 --> 00:03:00,780
The International Expo
was a great success.

16
00:03:00,847 --> 00:03:05,618
It was a festival of hopes and dreams.
This award is proof of it.

17
00:03:07,287 --> 00:03:09,422
It's thanks to all of you in Sales!

18
00:03:09,489 --> 00:03:10,523
Thank you!

19
00:03:14,594 --> 00:03:16,996
I say you'll be transferred
to HQ, next term.

20
00:03:17,063 --> 00:03:19,165
You're on the same track
as your older brother.

21
00:03:19,232 --> 00:03:20,600
We’ll see.

22
00:03:20,667 --> 00:03:24,170
No, it's basically decided.
We'll be sad once you're gone, Boss.

23
00:03:24,237 --> 00:03:26,773
Don't you mean to say, "Good riddance"?

24
00:03:31,211 --> 00:03:32,212
Hello.

25
00:03:34,247 --> 00:03:36,082
Don't come without an appointment!

26
00:03:37,850 --> 00:03:39,652
Metropolitan Police! Freeze!

27
00:03:40,587 --> 00:03:41,955
We have a search warrant.

28
00:03:46,226 --> 00:03:47,293
Is something wrong?

29
00:03:47,360 --> 00:03:48,928
You are Yuta Yoshii, correct?

30
00:03:48,995 --> 00:03:49,829
Yes.

31
00:03:49,896 --> 00:03:52,832
An arrest warrant has been issued
for you, for bribery.

32
00:03:53,499 --> 00:03:55,702
It's 2:08 p.m.
I'm placing you under arrest.

33
00:03:59,606 --> 00:04:03,443
We're doing detox cooking today,
to be beautiful in both mind and body.

34
00:04:04,644 --> 00:04:07,580
A healthy spirit comes from healthy meals.

35
00:04:07,647 --> 00:04:10,683
Today, based on Zen cuisine,
we'll cook using seasonal ingredients…

36
00:04:10,750 --> 00:04:12,418
I'm home!

37
00:04:13,019 --> 00:04:14,420
Welcome home.

38
00:04:14,487 --> 00:04:15,722
Good day.

39
00:04:15,788 --> 00:04:16,889
Good day.

40
00:04:16,956 --> 00:04:19,158
What a refined young lady.

41
00:04:19,225 --> 00:04:21,594
You must have raised her well.

42
00:04:21,661 --> 00:04:24,130
No, she isn't like this normally…

43
00:04:24,764 --> 00:04:26,366
IS THAT YOUR DAD ON THE NEWS?

44
00:04:26,432 --> 00:04:28,935
Now, a few tips for today's <i>Ganmodoki</i>.

45
00:04:29,002 --> 00:04:30,136
Okay.

46
00:04:30,203 --> 00:04:31,037
First…

47
00:04:31,104 --> 00:04:34,507
<i>- A search warrant has been executed…</i>
- Hey, don't turn on the TV during class.

48
00:04:34,574 --> 00:04:36,576
<i>…for bribing the Organizing Committee.</i>

49
00:04:36,643 --> 00:04:39,912
<i>The arrest was made at Tazawa Trading,</i>
<i>under Tazawa Group Holdings.</i>

50
00:04:39,979 --> 00:04:43,549
<i>A Mr. Yuta Yoshii, 51,</i>
<i>Manager of the First Sales Department.</i>

51
00:04:43,616 --> 00:04:50,323
<i>To secure the adoption of company products</i>
<i>for the expo held last November,</i>

52
00:04:50,390 --> 00:04:53,993
<i>Mr. Yoshii allegedly made donations</i>
<i>to the Organizing Committee.</i>

53
00:04:54,927 --> 00:04:56,629
<i>Were you in cahoots?</i>

54
00:04:56,696 --> 00:04:59,499
<i>In cahoots?</i>
<i>Teacher, you make it sound so bad.</i>

55
00:04:59,565 --> 00:05:01,334
<i>We're a team.</i>

56
00:05:01,401 --> 00:05:03,436
<i>I'm not one of you yet.</i>

57
00:05:04,103 --> 00:05:07,240
<i>- This is a setup!</i>
<i>- This can also be seen as justice!</i>

58
00:05:07,307 --> 00:05:08,675
<i>I didn't make you believe it.</i>

59
00:05:08,741 --> 00:05:10,143
<i>It was your own greed!</i>

60
00:05:13,646 --> 00:05:14,480
Cut!

61
00:05:15,648 --> 00:05:17,050
FILMING SCHEDULE - SEPTEMBER 16

62
00:05:21,788 --> 00:05:22,789
What time is it?

63
00:05:23,356 --> 00:05:24,624
It's 11:00 p.m.

64
00:05:26,192 --> 00:05:29,562
Well, okay. I'll give it the all clear.

65
00:05:29,629 --> 00:05:30,630
Okay.

66
00:05:30,697 --> 00:05:34,033
Okay, that's all for today!
Thank you, everyone!

67
00:05:34,100 --> 00:05:36,302
- Thank you.
- See you.

68
00:05:37,670 --> 00:05:41,607
This guy can only do expressions
he thinks will look cool, right?

69
00:05:42,108 --> 00:05:43,009
Director.

70
00:05:43,076 --> 00:05:44,077
Yes?

71
00:05:44,143 --> 00:05:45,278
A moment.

72
00:05:45,345 --> 00:05:46,279
Sure.

73
00:05:46,346 --> 00:05:50,383
No, that’s impossible! We can't return
to the original work's plot now…

74
00:05:50,450 --> 00:05:53,653
I know, but the fan backlash
is more than expected.

75
00:05:53,720 --> 00:05:57,190
We decided on it together!
That we would have an original plot.

76
00:05:57,256 --> 00:05:59,058
The author gave permission.

77
00:05:59,125 --> 00:06:01,394
In fact, they were happy about it, right?

78
00:06:01,461 --> 00:06:04,664
In this day and age,
the fans are scarier than the author.

79
00:06:04,731 --> 00:06:07,333
We must do what we can for now.

80
00:06:07,834 --> 00:06:09,502
The quality will drop.

81
00:06:10,336 --> 00:06:11,304
I cannot do it.

82
00:06:11,371 --> 00:06:13,439
I understand.

83
00:06:13,506 --> 00:06:17,643
It pains me to ask
this of you, Mr. Fujimaki.

84
00:06:17,710 --> 00:06:20,213
So, you should take a break

85
00:06:20,279 --> 00:06:22,615
and Assistant Director Takeuchi
will take over.

86
00:06:22,682 --> 00:06:23,983
What?

87
00:06:24,050 --> 00:06:26,285
Wait, am I being taken off the project?

88
00:06:26,352 --> 00:06:28,988
This project was my idea! Are you joking?

89
00:06:29,756 --> 00:06:32,291
To be honest, I’m not confident either.

90
00:06:32,358 --> 00:06:33,760
But I have to do it.

91
00:06:34,827 --> 00:06:37,196
I'll properly inherit your spirit,
Mr. Fujimaki!

92
00:06:37,263 --> 00:06:39,866
I don't remember giving you my spirit!

93
00:06:40,666 --> 00:06:41,601
What?

94
00:06:41,667 --> 00:06:45,338
Wait, isn't this a breach of contract?

95
00:06:46,005 --> 00:06:48,541
You shouted at the staff, right?

96
00:06:49,075 --> 00:06:52,278
No, it's a young cast…
things needed to be kept tight.

97
00:06:52,345 --> 00:06:56,649
You shouted "Hey!" loudly at Kanazawa.

98
00:06:56,716 --> 00:06:58,151
That's nothing to complain about--

99
00:06:58,217 --> 00:07:02,488
You called Ide an "idiot,"
Kamata and Ito "stupid" many times,

100
00:07:02,555 --> 00:07:05,091
and each a "moron" and "oaf" once.

101
00:07:05,958 --> 00:07:08,327
That's harassment, isn't it?

102
00:07:08,394 --> 00:07:09,429
No, but…

103
00:07:11,097 --> 00:07:13,132
Please wait in the back lobby.

104
00:07:13,199 --> 00:07:15,168
Thank you very much.

105
00:07:19,138 --> 00:07:21,374
AOBA PHARMACY

106
00:07:21,441 --> 00:07:22,909
The daily login is in two hours!

107
00:07:22,975 --> 00:07:24,444
Wait, this is bad.

108
00:07:24,510 --> 00:07:25,745
Only 30 minutes left.

109
00:07:25,812 --> 00:07:27,313
You should've said that earlier.

110
00:07:27,380 --> 00:07:30,149
Let's dash home!
Begin the battle to login!

111
00:07:30,216 --> 00:07:31,083
- Yes!
- Yes!

112
00:07:32,185 --> 00:07:34,053
Let's gather once home.

113
00:07:34,120 --> 00:07:35,721
Get on comms!

114
00:07:36,722 --> 00:07:38,257
Run!

115
00:08:11,757 --> 00:08:12,925
Put your back into it!

116
00:08:15,495 --> 00:08:16,762
Be careful.

117
00:08:28,674 --> 00:08:29,976
It's just a deer.

118
00:08:33,412 --> 00:08:34,680
Ms. Nishino!

119
00:09:07,547 --> 00:09:09,315
Hello, sir.

120
00:09:10,283 --> 00:09:13,319
Not being allowed a visit
for ten days. That's inhumane.

121
00:09:13,386 --> 00:09:15,755
It’s no big deal. How is the company?

122
00:09:15,821 --> 00:09:20,059
I'm keeping things running in your stead.

123
00:09:20,126 --> 00:09:21,661
Acting Manager…

124
00:09:21,727 --> 00:09:24,030
Your wife and daughter
are also keeping calm.

125
00:09:24,096 --> 00:09:25,798
Right, thank you.

126
00:09:29,268 --> 00:09:30,770
I haven't said a word.

127
00:09:32,305 --> 00:09:35,041
I know. I trust you.

128
00:09:35,608 --> 00:09:37,677
They were all legal donations.

129
00:09:38,210 --> 00:09:42,114
Manager, you were framed.
Someone sold you out behind the scenes.

130
00:09:43,282 --> 00:09:45,151
Traitors are everywhere.

131
00:09:45,217 --> 00:09:48,087
Our lawyer also says
the police jumped the gun.

132
00:09:48,588 --> 00:09:49,922
You will not be indicted.

133
00:09:50,790 --> 00:09:52,358
When can I get out?

134
00:09:53,292 --> 00:09:55,328
Our entire group is pressuring the cops.

135
00:09:56,062 --> 00:09:58,598
You should be released in two days.

136
00:09:59,799 --> 00:10:02,735
I need to meet Mr. Kagami,
to explain things.

137
00:10:02,802 --> 00:10:06,205
The police haven't made a move
against the company yet.

138
00:10:07,506 --> 00:10:10,676
It's better if you don't make contact.
I’ll handle the apologies.

139
00:10:12,745 --> 00:10:15,715
Don't leave the house
even after you're released. Got it?

140
00:10:16,282 --> 00:10:18,517
Don't look at social media either.

141
00:10:19,185 --> 00:10:20,953
Delete your accounts.

142
00:10:23,723 --> 00:10:24,724
Okay.

143
00:10:28,094 --> 00:10:31,130
CHILDREN UNDER 12 NOW 2400 YEN

144
00:10:37,970 --> 00:10:40,272
DISCOUNT FOR GRADE SCHOOLERS

145
00:10:43,709 --> 00:10:45,277
Kisuke!

146
00:10:50,483 --> 00:10:54,153
Kisuke. Help me.

147
00:10:54,820 --> 00:10:58,524
- That person is bullying me.
- I had her take her medicine.

148
00:10:58,591 --> 00:10:59,925
Did she bite you?

149
00:10:59,992 --> 00:11:01,460
Oh, it's no big deal.

150
00:11:01,527 --> 00:11:03,496
Mother.

151
00:11:03,562 --> 00:11:05,731
I won't be fooled.

152
00:11:05,798 --> 00:11:08,100
That person is trying to kill me.

153
00:11:09,068 --> 00:11:10,102
You murderer!

154
00:11:11,404 --> 00:11:12,705
What happened to Saito?

155
00:11:12,772 --> 00:11:18,277
You said you hated him,
so we switched him for a veteran!

156
00:11:18,344 --> 00:11:21,147
Ms. Shoko, shall we go for a walk?

157
00:11:21,647 --> 00:11:22,648
How about it?

158
00:11:23,749 --> 00:11:25,084
No way!

159
00:11:25,851 --> 00:11:26,686
Ms. Shoko!

160
00:11:50,309 --> 00:11:52,778
MITAKA GUEST HOUSE

161
00:11:53,412 --> 00:11:55,781
"Ruiner of original works…"

162
00:11:55,848 --> 00:11:57,483
"Never make anything again."

163
00:11:58,084 --> 00:12:00,886
"No respect for the source material."

164
00:12:01,487 --> 00:12:05,224
You critics should mind
your damn business!

165
00:12:07,193 --> 00:12:11,230
You’re destroying the industry
with your lack of knowledge.

166
00:12:19,472 --> 00:12:21,907
KINPO

167
00:12:21,974 --> 00:12:23,142
"To Chen.

168
00:12:23,809 --> 00:12:25,377
Did you see this news?

169
00:12:25,444 --> 00:12:29,248
A familiar place
made me suddenly think of you all.

170
00:12:29,782 --> 00:12:31,717
I would like to see you,
after all this time."

171
00:12:33,419 --> 00:12:34,453
Kinpo?

172
00:12:40,459 --> 00:12:41,660
Huh?

173
00:12:49,135 --> 00:12:50,936
I'm just asking this to be sure,

174
00:12:51,437 --> 00:12:55,274
your arrest won't affect
my university entrance exam, right?

175
00:12:55,341 --> 00:12:57,076
I already explained.

176
00:12:57,143 --> 00:13:00,146
I didn't do anything wrong.
The police made a mistake.

177
00:13:00,212 --> 00:13:02,381
Focus on your studies.

178
00:13:02,448 --> 00:13:05,751
But if you're indicted,
over 99% of Japanese trials…

179
00:13:05,818 --> 00:13:08,120
I told you I won't be indicted!

180
00:13:13,492 --> 00:13:14,760
I'm off.

181
00:13:15,461 --> 00:13:16,796
Have a good day.

182
00:13:24,336 --> 00:13:25,237
I’ll help.

183
00:13:28,307 --> 00:13:29,508
Don't worry.

184
00:13:31,477 --> 00:13:35,447
Between the police and the Tazawa Group,
which do you think is more powerful?

185
00:13:36,081 --> 00:13:38,717
If we keep protesting,
the police can't do anything.

186
00:13:41,020 --> 00:13:43,956
I have a class today,
so can you stay outside?

187
00:13:45,858 --> 00:13:48,160
I was told not to go out.

188
00:13:49,628 --> 00:13:52,064
YUTA YOSHII

189
00:13:52,131 --> 00:13:53,866
"He finally got found out."

190
00:13:53,933 --> 00:13:56,268
"I saw him on TV,
he has a villain's face."

191
00:14:01,407 --> 00:14:02,541
KINPO

192
00:14:02,608 --> 00:14:04,910
"Did you see this news?

193
00:14:04,977 --> 00:14:09,081
"A familiar place
made me suddenly think of you all.

194
00:14:09,715 --> 00:14:12,017
I would like to see you,
after all this time."

195
00:14:12,084 --> 00:14:13,085
Kinpo?

196
00:14:13,686 --> 00:14:15,321
FROM KINPO

197
00:14:16,121 --> 00:14:18,257
HUMAN BONES FOUND ON CONSTRUCTION SITE
TANBE CITY

198
00:14:18,324 --> 00:14:19,558
Tanbe City?

199
00:15:11,110 --> 00:15:13,946
Oh, welcome. This way, please.

200
00:15:16,548 --> 00:15:19,551
- Let me take your jacket.
- Sure.

201
00:15:24,290 --> 00:15:27,893
TANBE CITY SEPTEMBER 1988

202
00:15:30,329 --> 00:15:32,431
WELCOME! TANBE CENTRAL SHOPPING DISTRICT

203
00:15:32,498 --> 00:15:34,900
SHOE SHOP SENDAIYA
LADIES' SHOES SPECIAL SALE!

204
00:15:34,967 --> 00:15:36,902
HALF PRICE

205
00:15:44,476 --> 00:15:45,644
- Bye!
- Goodbye!

206
00:15:45,711 --> 00:15:46,912
TANBE MIDDLE SCHOOL

207
00:15:58,724 --> 00:16:02,161
Yuta Yoshii. I hear they
kicked you out of the baseball club?

208
00:16:04,129 --> 00:16:05,831
Hey, why not join the Movie Club?

209
00:16:05,898 --> 00:16:08,434
We’re starting a new Movie Research Club.

210
00:16:09,034 --> 00:16:11,637
Because they crushed
our Manga Research Club.

211
00:16:11,704 --> 00:16:15,140
We need four members and an advisor,

212
00:16:15,207 --> 00:16:17,810
and it would be great
to have you star in our movies.

213
00:16:17,876 --> 00:16:19,411
I bet girls will join too.

214
00:16:22,448 --> 00:16:25,217
I’m not an otaku like you guys.

215
00:16:25,284 --> 00:16:26,752
- What?
- What?

216
00:16:26,819 --> 00:16:29,989
O-ta-ku. Don't you know?

217
00:16:30,055 --> 00:16:31,757
They call people like you "otaku."

218
00:16:31,824 --> 00:16:36,328
You're in middle school, yet you obsess
over manga, anime and movies.

219
00:16:36,395 --> 00:16:37,696
Those geeky--

220
00:16:37,763 --> 00:16:41,633
- Don't call us otaku! Don't stereotype us!
- You'll tear my shirt! Let go!

221
00:16:41,700 --> 00:16:43,902
No way! You started it!

222
00:16:43,969 --> 00:16:45,371
I told you, let go!

223
00:16:45,437 --> 00:16:46,739
- Never!
- Stop this.

224
00:16:47,606 --> 00:16:49,742
- Who cares!
- It hurts!

225
00:16:51,076 --> 00:16:53,479
- Are you okay?
- So nice to be full of energy.

226
00:16:53,545 --> 00:16:54,947
- Who is she?
- No clue.

227
00:16:55,514 --> 00:16:59,151
Michiru Miyashita, filling in for Mrs.
Koda while she's on maternity leave.

228
00:16:59,218 --> 00:17:00,319
Nice to meet you.

229
00:17:07,259 --> 00:17:09,762
- She's just like Matilda.
- True.

230
00:17:13,065 --> 00:17:14,199
Kick it back to us!

231
00:17:27,579 --> 00:17:28,847
What?

232
00:17:31,750 --> 00:17:34,186
Movie Research Club? Who was in it?

233
00:17:34,253 --> 00:17:38,023
I had completely forgotten it myself,

234
00:17:38,090 --> 00:17:41,326
but I really was in it for a while,
back in eighth grade.

235
00:17:41,393 --> 00:17:42,828
Doesn't sound like you.

236
00:17:42,895 --> 00:17:45,364
I thought you were all about baseball.

237
00:17:46,131 --> 00:17:49,501
There was a small commotion
at a local construction site recently,

238
00:17:49,568 --> 00:17:53,572
and one of my friends got nostalgic,
so he asked to meet.

239
00:17:53,639 --> 00:17:57,676
I bet that was just an excuse.
They want to meet to cheer you up.

240
00:17:57,743 --> 00:18:00,345
They can't just start off by saying
they saw you got arrested.

241
00:18:00,412 --> 00:18:01,547
Right?

242
00:18:01,613 --> 00:18:03,482
- That's nice of them.
- You should go.

243
00:18:03,549 --> 00:18:07,019
It has been 36… 37 years.
What will we talk about?

244
00:18:07,086 --> 00:18:09,254
I only vaguely remember their faces.

245
00:18:11,723 --> 00:18:13,225
Oh, I'll get it.

246
00:18:19,665 --> 00:18:20,933
He should go.

247
00:18:20,999 --> 00:18:22,401
Right? It sounds fun.

248
00:18:22,468 --> 00:18:23,869
Court-ordered mail!

249
00:18:24,603 --> 00:18:26,705
Please sign here.

250
00:18:27,406 --> 00:18:29,808
TOKYO DISTRICT COURT

251
00:18:52,064 --> 00:18:54,600
INDICTMENT

252
00:19:03,008 --> 00:19:06,945
I know I said and did things
that went overboard.

253
00:19:07,012 --> 00:19:09,481
Maybe I was too fired up and lost my cool.

254
00:19:10,082 --> 00:19:12,050
But I had an idea.

255
00:19:12,117 --> 00:19:14,052
We can still fix things
from episode seven, right?

256
00:19:14,119 --> 00:19:17,556
If we adjust the dialogue, we can
smoothly return to the original plot.

257
00:19:17,623 --> 00:19:20,192
Oh, wait a second. In the script…

258
00:19:20,259 --> 00:19:23,228
In episode seven, where was it…

259
00:19:26,832 --> 00:19:27,900
Did he go home?

260
00:19:27,966 --> 00:19:29,268
Yeah, thank goodness.

261
00:19:29,334 --> 00:19:32,571
He probably won't accept it,
but after you took over,

262
00:19:32,638 --> 00:19:34,706
the atmosphere on set improved.

263
00:19:34,773 --> 00:19:36,742
It was so tense before.

264
00:19:37,409 --> 00:19:40,746
He’s not a bad person,
but his thinking is old-fashioned.

265
00:19:40,812 --> 00:19:43,315
So he just can't help it.

266
00:19:43,382 --> 00:19:45,651
What will happen to Mr. Fujimaki?

267
00:19:45,717 --> 00:19:48,153
I think it will be tough for him.

268
00:19:48,854 --> 00:19:51,757
He had a period where he made good films.

269
00:19:51,823 --> 00:19:54,026
<i>Those Who Eat Soba </i>was a masterpiece.

270
00:19:54,092 --> 00:19:55,460
Oh, really?

271
00:19:56,061 --> 00:19:58,964
- What if he comes back?
- Give me a break.

272
00:20:19,518 --> 00:20:23,956
"I’ve taken over the family business
and now run a small barber shop.

273
00:20:24,022 --> 00:20:28,093
If you like, why not come by
for a haircut sometime?"

274
00:20:28,994 --> 00:20:30,195
Kinpo.

275
00:20:34,967 --> 00:20:36,368
He has arrived.

276
00:20:38,870 --> 00:20:39,705
Hey.

277
00:20:41,006 --> 00:20:42,474
Oh, sit down.

278
00:20:42,541 --> 00:20:43,508
Yes.

279
00:20:43,575 --> 00:20:44,676
Well…

280
00:20:45,677 --> 00:20:50,949
Sorry to make you travel
while you are recovering.

281
00:20:51,016 --> 00:20:54,019
Oh, it's fine.
I also need to walk a little.

282
00:20:54,086 --> 00:20:55,254
Right.

283
00:20:55,854 --> 00:21:00,092
I'm not allowed to drink alcohol,
so I'll have some orange juice.

284
00:21:00,158 --> 00:21:01,293
Understood.

285
00:21:02,227 --> 00:21:05,964
I am very sorry for the trouble
my younger brother has caused.

286
00:21:06,898 --> 00:21:10,302
It’s hard to believe,
but he’s been indicted.

287
00:21:10,969 --> 00:21:15,040
Our Totsuka and Sakurai
were also taken in for questioning.

288
00:21:15,607 --> 00:21:19,411
Well, I’m probably the final target.

289
00:21:19,478 --> 00:21:21,847
No, such a situation must be prevented.

290
00:21:21,913 --> 00:21:23,815
The briber must confess first,

291
00:21:24,316 --> 00:21:27,886
so as long as my brother doesn't crack,
no trouble will reach you, sir.

292
00:21:27,953 --> 00:21:30,155
I will stop it myself--

293
00:21:30,222 --> 00:21:31,556
Sorry for the wait.

294
00:21:38,730 --> 00:21:39,831
Thank you.

295
00:21:49,908 --> 00:21:50,809
Can we win?

296
00:21:51,877 --> 00:21:55,981
This indictment is unjust.
I will definitely win.

297
00:21:56,048 --> 00:21:57,049
Okay.

298
00:21:57,549 --> 00:22:00,752
Must be hard for you too.
Just when things were looking up…

299
00:22:02,120 --> 00:22:06,325
It might affect your wife's work too.

300
00:22:06,391 --> 00:22:10,228
Oh, and I hear your daughter
is about to enter university?

301
00:22:11,129 --> 00:22:13,632
You must be so anxious.

302
00:22:14,132 --> 00:22:18,770
I, Rokuro Kagami, will do all I can.

303
00:22:20,072 --> 00:22:22,174
You are too kind.

304
00:22:35,487 --> 00:22:37,556
Want to go play pachinko?
I'm feeling lucky!

305
00:22:37,622 --> 00:22:39,057
I'll definitely win.

306
00:22:39,124 --> 00:22:41,193
Watch it, old man.

307
00:22:41,259 --> 00:22:42,761
You lowlifes.

308
00:22:43,295 --> 00:22:45,664
- Hey, hold it there.
- What did you say?

309
00:22:46,698 --> 00:22:49,134
What did you just call us, old man?

310
00:23:00,879 --> 00:23:01,980
Ouch…

311
00:23:15,193 --> 00:23:18,797
WHY NOT COME BY FOR A HAIRCUT SOMETIME?

312
00:23:31,143 --> 00:23:37,616
KIKUHARA SALON

313
00:23:43,221 --> 00:23:45,357
Oh, it has been a while.

314
00:23:45,424 --> 00:23:48,927
I’m Yuta Yoshii, the one you contacted.
Long time, no see.

315
00:23:50,228 --> 00:23:51,430
Hello.

316
00:24:00,572 --> 00:24:01,440
Welcome.

317
00:24:06,278 --> 00:24:09,080
You are… Kisuke Kikuhara.

318
00:24:09,147 --> 00:24:10,015
Kinpo!

319
00:24:16,455 --> 00:24:18,590
I figured you would have
a bit of a belly by now.

320
00:24:18,657 --> 00:24:21,059
Hajime Fujimaki. Chen.

321
00:24:26,832 --> 00:24:28,867
You’re still as cool as ever, Yun.

322
00:24:32,871 --> 00:24:35,240
Wow, it has been a long time.

323
00:24:35,307 --> 00:24:37,275
You two haven't changed.

324
00:24:39,244 --> 00:24:40,579
Who was that man earlier?

325
00:24:40,645 --> 00:24:42,080
Just a customer.

326
00:24:42,147 --> 00:24:45,517
He clearly looked like he was in his 60s.

327
00:24:45,584 --> 00:24:47,285
No wonder he didn't look familiar.

328
00:24:48,820 --> 00:24:51,089
Hey, what happened to you?

329
00:24:51,156 --> 00:24:54,192
I’ve been getting injured
constantly since middle school.

330
00:24:54,259 --> 00:24:55,494
You!

331
00:24:57,562 --> 00:24:59,564
CLUB REGISTRATION FORM
MOVIE RESEARCH CLUB

332
00:24:59,631 --> 00:25:00,866
ADVISOR: MICHIRU MIYASHITA

333
00:25:00,932 --> 00:25:02,734
That’s a nice pen.

334
00:25:08,039 --> 00:25:11,443
This is my original character, "Ton-chan."

335
00:25:14,379 --> 00:25:15,380
Here.

336
00:25:17,082 --> 00:25:18,617
Thank you.

337
00:25:20,318 --> 00:25:22,153
I can't do it for long, okay?

338
00:25:23,255 --> 00:25:24,923
HAJIME FUJIMAKI, CLASS 2E
KISUKE KIKUHARA,CLASS 2G

339
00:25:24,990 --> 00:25:26,224
Aren't you joining?

340
00:25:30,161 --> 00:25:31,563
- I…
- We don't need him.

341
00:25:37,736 --> 00:25:40,839
Don't tell anyone the reason
I came to the nurses' office.

342
00:25:48,113 --> 00:25:50,782
Matilda is our advisor!

343
00:25:50,849 --> 00:25:51,917
Amazing.

344
00:25:51,983 --> 00:25:53,785
Who is Matilda?

345
00:25:54,486 --> 00:25:56,421
I prefer Fraw Bow.

346
00:25:56,488 --> 00:26:01,092
You must like Sayla, right?
That's why you're still just a little boy.

347
00:26:01,760 --> 00:26:04,963
Matilda is a real mature woman.

348
00:26:08,600 --> 00:26:10,068
Ms. Matilda!

349
00:26:11,136 --> 00:26:12,771
Ms. Matilda.

350
00:26:14,005 --> 00:26:15,640
Ms. Matilda!

351
00:26:31,156 --> 00:26:32,824
The best woman has got to be…

352
00:26:33,525 --> 00:26:34,626
Crowley Hamon.

353
00:26:39,197 --> 00:26:42,334
<i>This is an announcement</i>
<i>from the Tanbe City Office.</i>

354
00:26:42,400 --> 00:26:44,436
<i>- A smog alert has been issued.</i>
- She likes <i>Gundam </i>too.

355
00:26:44,502 --> 00:26:46,037
She said Hamon, right?

356
00:26:46,104 --> 00:26:47,739
She knows all about it!

357
00:26:47,806 --> 00:26:51,209
What should we do?
Don't you want to talk about <i>Gundam</i>?

358
00:26:51,276 --> 00:26:52,911
- I do!
- So crazy!

359
00:27:02,287 --> 00:27:06,625
<i>I haven't been to Tanbe</i>
<i>since graduating middle school.</i>

360
00:27:06,691 --> 00:27:08,193
<i>Me too, no reason to go.</i>

361
00:27:08,259 --> 00:27:10,295
<i>It's the same for me.</i>

362
00:27:18,970 --> 00:27:20,872
It’s like a different town.

363
00:27:22,140 --> 00:27:24,509
That park
is where the chemical factory was.

364
00:27:24,576 --> 00:27:27,912
So that means… That street
used to be the shopping district!

365
00:27:27,979 --> 00:27:30,015
Around that building
was Chen’s construction shop.

366
00:27:30,081 --> 00:27:32,450
- Further down was my barber shop.
- Right.

367
00:27:32,517 --> 00:27:35,787
Then where was my housing complex?
That apartment building?

368
00:27:35,854 --> 00:27:38,390
Wait, what about our middle school?

369
00:27:38,456 --> 00:27:41,059
Seems it got merged and moved a while ago.

370
00:27:41,126 --> 00:27:42,794
Now, it’s a shopping mall.

371
00:27:42,861 --> 00:27:45,463
They really expanded the station plaza.

372
00:27:45,530 --> 00:27:49,401
With the train lines, this is now
a commuter town. The air is cleaner.

373
00:27:49,467 --> 00:27:52,871
You could call it
the "New Happiness Town, Tanbe."

374
00:27:52,937 --> 00:27:54,906
Hooray for redevelopment.

375
00:27:56,174 --> 00:27:57,575
Oh!

376
00:27:57,642 --> 00:28:01,546
Now that it has changed so much,
it doesn't feel nostalgic anymore.

377
00:28:03,415 --> 00:28:05,283
Shall we go to the police station?

378
00:28:05,350 --> 00:28:06,351
Police?

379
00:28:06,418 --> 00:28:10,088
I want to hear what happened
to those bones they found.

380
00:28:10,922 --> 00:28:12,290
Why?

381
00:28:12,357 --> 00:28:15,393
I'm just curious.

382
00:28:15,460 --> 00:28:18,963
Fine by me. It might serve
as material for my work.

383
00:28:19,864 --> 00:28:20,932
Let's go.

384
00:28:32,811 --> 00:28:34,979
In short, we aren't sure
if it's even a case,

385
00:28:35,046 --> 00:28:37,248
so we have no plans for an investigation.

386
00:28:37,315 --> 00:28:38,717
But they're human bones.

387
00:28:38,783 --> 00:28:43,755
We don't know how old they are,
they could be from World War II or older.

388
00:28:43,822 --> 00:28:46,357
They could have washed up
from a nearby cemetery.

389
00:28:46,424 --> 00:28:48,560
Isn't it the police's job
to investigate that?

390
00:28:49,127 --> 00:28:52,063
It is, if there was a relevant
missing person's report,

391
00:28:52,130 --> 00:28:53,431
but there wasn't one.

392
00:28:54,232 --> 00:28:56,334
Where were the bones found, specifically?

393
00:28:57,368 --> 00:28:59,771
Sorry, we aren't allowed
to disclose that either.

394
00:29:00,271 --> 00:29:03,341
In other words,
though he can't say it clearly,

395
00:29:03,408 --> 00:29:05,276
if they investigate
any construction stops,

396
00:29:05,343 --> 00:29:09,614
the contractors are in trouble,
and the police have more work.

397
00:29:09,681 --> 00:29:11,516
No one wins.

398
00:29:11,583 --> 00:29:16,087
Cases like this are often buried,
without even a report.

399
00:29:16,154 --> 00:29:16,988
Right?

400
00:29:17,055 --> 00:29:18,256
I can't say anything.

401
00:29:19,924 --> 00:29:20,959
Thank you very much.

402
00:29:21,025 --> 00:29:22,327
Let's go.

403
00:29:22,393 --> 00:29:24,696
TANBE POLICE STATION

404
00:29:24,763 --> 00:29:27,332
Since we're here, let's go there too.

405
00:29:27,398 --> 00:29:30,168
It's outside the redevelopment area,
it might still be there.

406
00:29:30,235 --> 00:29:31,436
Where is "there"?

407
00:29:32,070 --> 00:29:34,038
Video Jupiter, of course.

408
00:29:34,105 --> 00:29:35,640
Our clubroom.

409
00:29:38,777 --> 00:29:39,844
All right.

410
00:29:40,845 --> 00:29:44,015
What? No way, you mean
you haven't even seen <i>Project A</i>?

411
00:29:44,082 --> 00:29:47,485
- It’s a Hong Kong action cinema wonder.
- The action in <i>Kung-Fu Master </i>is better.

412
00:29:47,552 --> 00:29:49,521
Jackie versus Benny Urquidez was peak.

413
00:29:49,587 --> 00:29:51,956
Watch <i>Police Story </i>and <i>Armour of God </i>too.

414
00:29:52,023 --> 00:29:55,126
I can't watch stuff like that.
TV is only one hour a day at my house.

415
00:29:55,193 --> 00:29:57,629
Then you aren't qualified
to join the club.

416
00:29:58,129 --> 00:30:01,166
Oh, damn, someone else rented it again.

417
00:30:02,066 --> 00:30:04,636
No one is at my home today.
Let's watch it there.

418
00:30:04,702 --> 00:30:05,870
- Nice.
- Let's go.

419
00:30:05,937 --> 00:30:07,372
Hurry up!

420
00:30:15,346 --> 00:30:18,149
It's a coffee chain now.

421
00:30:18,850 --> 00:30:23,121
Rental videos were all the rage back then,
now it's an endangered species.

422
00:30:23,922 --> 00:30:25,757
Nothing lasts forever.

423
00:30:25,824 --> 00:30:28,426
Oh, but look, that the building
is even still standing

424
00:30:28,493 --> 00:30:30,428
is a miracle, right?

425
00:30:40,705 --> 00:30:42,540
Sorry for the wait.

426
00:30:44,075 --> 00:30:45,743
Sorry for the wait.

427
00:30:46,744 --> 00:30:47,745
All right.

428
00:30:51,182 --> 00:30:52,584
Sorry for the wait.

429
00:30:53,151 --> 00:30:54,919
- Who ordered an Americano?
- Me.

430
00:30:54,986 --> 00:30:55,820
Okay.

431
00:30:55,887 --> 00:30:56,955
I ordered a cafe latte.

432
00:30:57,021 --> 00:30:58,389
- Sweet bean coffee.
- Yes.

433
00:31:03,494 --> 00:31:04,629
Oh?

434
00:31:05,396 --> 00:31:07,198
Take your time.

435
00:31:07,265 --> 00:31:09,734
Is that your real name?

436
00:31:09,801 --> 00:31:11,135
"Hakuba."

437
00:31:11,202 --> 00:31:13,204
Is that your first name? "White Horse"?

438
00:31:13,271 --> 00:31:14,305
Yes.

439
00:31:14,372 --> 00:31:15,607
Truly a Heisei kid.

440
00:31:15,673 --> 00:31:18,509
All my daughters' friends
have names I can't read.

441
00:31:18,576 --> 00:31:19,410
You're a local?

442
00:31:20,578 --> 00:31:24,215
I commute from Tokyo to the Engineering
Department at the university here.

443
00:31:24,282 --> 00:31:26,784
Look, asking personal information
for no reason…

444
00:31:26,851 --> 00:31:29,220
That's a bad habit old men have. Sorry.

445
00:31:29,287 --> 00:31:33,124
- I'm actually in "communication training."
- Communication training?

446
00:31:33,825 --> 00:31:36,928
I have no people skills,
so I'm training by doing customer service.

447
00:31:37,795 --> 00:31:39,063
Communication training?

448
00:31:39,130 --> 00:31:41,532
So she wants us to talk to her!

449
00:31:43,134 --> 00:31:45,703
We used to live in this town
when we were kids.

450
00:31:47,238 --> 00:31:48,506
Oh, okay!

451
00:31:48,573 --> 00:31:52,577
There was a huge chemical factory
in the middle of town. It's a park now.

452
00:31:52,644 --> 00:31:55,613
Back then, there were photochemical
smog warnings all the time!

453
00:31:55,680 --> 00:31:57,782
We used to call it
the "poison gas factory."

454
00:31:57,849 --> 00:32:01,653
Then, they redeveloped the town
to move that factory away.

455
00:32:01,719 --> 00:32:03,888
It was right in the middle
of the bubble era,

456
00:32:03,955 --> 00:32:07,158
there was massive construction,
and our houses were evicted then too.

457
00:32:07,225 --> 00:32:10,929
It has been, what, 36 years?

458
00:32:10,995 --> 00:32:13,031
Everything has changed.

459
00:32:18,236 --> 00:32:19,704
"Oh, I see!"

460
00:32:19,771 --> 00:32:21,239
"I didn't know that."

461
00:32:21,306 --> 00:32:23,441
That's how you deal
with stories you don't care about.

462
00:32:23,508 --> 00:32:25,910
It makes us old guys happy
and order more coffee.

463
00:32:27,578 --> 00:32:30,615
So you're childhood friends,
and you still meet like this…

464
00:32:31,182 --> 00:32:32,250
That's wonderful.

465
00:32:32,850 --> 00:32:34,752
We're just old men, nothing wonderful.

466
00:32:34,819 --> 00:32:37,322
This shop used to be a rental video store.

467
00:32:37,388 --> 00:32:41,426
The shelves were lined up like this…
not DVDs, but VHS.

468
00:32:41,492 --> 00:32:43,461
- They had Betamax too.
- Right.

469
00:32:43,528 --> 00:32:44,963
I see.

470
00:32:45,029 --> 00:32:47,665
In middle school,
we were in the Movie Research Club.

471
00:32:47,732 --> 00:32:50,735
There was a break room in the back.
Oh, is it still there?

472
00:32:50,802 --> 00:32:53,838
The manager was kind enough
to let us use it as a clubroom.

473
00:32:54,405 --> 00:32:55,740
That's unthinkable nowadays.

474
00:32:55,807 --> 00:32:58,643
Do you want to see it?
It's a storage room now.

475
00:32:58,710 --> 00:32:59,644
Yes.

476
00:32:59,711 --> 00:33:01,012
No, I'm fine.

477
00:33:02,213 --> 00:33:04,048
We hung out there every day,

478
00:33:04,115 --> 00:33:07,518
filming all over town making a movie.

479
00:33:08,086 --> 00:33:12,190
When you were in middle school,
was it on film?

480
00:33:12,256 --> 00:33:16,627
Right, they were called "moving pictures."
Still silent back then.

481
00:33:16,694 --> 00:33:18,396
She'll believe you!

482
00:33:18,463 --> 00:33:21,232
Home video cameras
had just been released back then,

483
00:33:21,299 --> 00:33:24,635
so anyone could film easily.

484
00:33:25,636 --> 00:33:26,771
He was the star.

485
00:33:26,838 --> 00:33:28,539
Oh, what kind of movie was it?

486
00:33:29,607 --> 00:33:31,476
Actually, I don't remember.

487
00:33:31,542 --> 00:33:34,078
Since we're here, why not try doing it?

488
00:33:34,145 --> 00:33:34,979
Doing what?

489
00:33:35,046 --> 00:33:38,182
Try acting out what kind of movie it was.

490
00:33:38,249 --> 00:33:42,186
You're joking. It's too embarrassing,
doing it in public like this.

491
00:33:42,253 --> 00:33:45,490
You seem pretty motivated. I'm out.
I don't remember anyway.

492
00:33:45,556 --> 00:33:46,924
Come on, just do it.

493
00:34:09,047 --> 00:34:11,082
Ouch, it hurts! I heard a snap.

494
00:34:11,149 --> 00:34:12,650
- I'm shaking.
- Did you hear it?

495
00:34:12,717 --> 00:34:14,519
Sorry, I didn't.

496
00:34:14,585 --> 00:34:17,288
- It hurts.
- The movie was like that.

497
00:34:17,355 --> 00:34:18,389
Oh, I see.

498
00:34:19,590 --> 00:34:21,826
Was it some sort of contemporary dance?

499
00:34:21,893 --> 00:34:23,828
Well, I guess so.

500
00:34:23,895 --> 00:34:26,831
We made artistic works
depicting the inner world.

501
00:34:26,898 --> 00:34:28,566
Maybe influenced by David Lynch.

502
00:34:28,633 --> 00:34:31,402
That’s amazing. Oh, was it well received?

503
00:34:31,903 --> 00:34:33,271
Was it?

504
00:34:34,439 --> 00:34:35,339
Oh, wait.

505
00:34:35,840 --> 00:34:36,874
I remember.

506
00:34:36,941 --> 00:34:39,077
We rented the community center
for a screening.

507
00:34:39,143 --> 00:34:40,545
We got quite a few viewers.

508
00:34:40,611 --> 00:34:43,781
So strange. There were
a lot of people in this town.

509
00:34:43,848 --> 00:34:44,949
Yes.

510
00:34:49,153 --> 00:34:51,422
MOVIE SCREENING THIS WAY

511
00:34:51,489 --> 00:34:53,191
All right, looks good.

512
00:34:53,257 --> 00:34:54,725
You went too far.

513
00:34:54,792 --> 00:34:56,861
Okay. Right there.

514
00:35:02,600 --> 00:35:03,468
It's done.

515
00:35:03,534 --> 00:35:04,469
Yuta.

516
00:35:05,536 --> 00:35:07,305
There are a lot of people.

517
00:35:07,371 --> 00:35:08,840
Even people we don't know.

518
00:35:08,906 --> 00:35:10,641
They're here for the Koshien star.

519
00:35:10,708 --> 00:35:13,611
- Cut it out.
- There aren't enough chairs.

520
00:35:13,678 --> 00:35:15,246
I'll get some from the town hall.

521
00:35:15,313 --> 00:35:17,648
- I'll help too.
- Thanks, Dad, big brother.

522
00:35:17,715 --> 00:35:20,251
- Kento, let's go.
- Yes.

523
00:35:20,318 --> 00:35:21,419
Can't wait.

524
00:35:23,020 --> 00:35:24,589
- Cheers!
- Cheers.

525
00:35:24,655 --> 00:35:28,559
Mom, Dad, don't drink here!

526
00:35:28,626 --> 00:35:29,794
Is beer not allowed?

527
00:35:29,861 --> 00:35:31,162
Oh, I'll give you this.

528
00:35:31,229 --> 00:35:33,631
Fried chicken to share with everyone.

529
00:35:33,698 --> 00:35:35,600
- Here, eat up.
- Thank you.

530
00:35:36,134 --> 00:35:37,034
Mom!

531
00:35:38,536 --> 00:35:39,437
Your seat is here.

532
00:35:39,504 --> 00:35:41,572
Sorry, I had a guest.

533
00:35:42,073 --> 00:35:45,143
Fujimaki, Yoshii,
thank you for looking after him.

534
00:35:45,810 --> 00:35:47,612
I brought <i>inari </i>sushi!

535
00:35:47,678 --> 00:35:49,347
- Thank you!
- Thank you.

536
00:35:49,413 --> 00:35:51,048
Yun, your girlfriend is here.

537
00:35:54,085 --> 00:35:56,087
- She isn't my girlfriend.
- Hurry up!

538
00:35:59,490 --> 00:36:00,358
You came.

539
00:36:00,925 --> 00:36:03,027
Well, I was also in the movie.

540
00:36:05,429 --> 00:36:06,364
Hey!

541
00:36:07,398 --> 00:36:09,567
Why don't I have a seat?

542
00:36:09,634 --> 00:36:11,936
Do you want me to stand and watch?

543
00:36:12,003 --> 00:36:14,639
Why is that idiot Hachiro here?

544
00:36:15,206 --> 00:36:16,107
What?

545
00:36:16,674 --> 00:36:19,076
What did you say, bastard?

546
00:36:20,444 --> 00:36:22,813
- What?
- Just stand and watch, it's fine.

547
00:36:22,880 --> 00:36:24,348
Shut up, old man.

548
00:36:24,916 --> 00:36:28,152
It hurts! Hey, it hurts, damn it, old man!

549
00:36:28,219 --> 00:36:31,022
- Don't hurt me each time I say "old man"!
- Rambo.

550
00:36:31,956 --> 00:36:34,158
That man is no ordinary person.

551
00:36:34,225 --> 00:36:36,427
He has definitely killed someone.

552
00:36:48,039 --> 00:36:50,374
Sorry, don't stand around here!

553
00:36:50,441 --> 00:36:52,610
If you're coming in, please come in.

554
00:36:52,677 --> 00:36:53,811
Why are so many coming?

555
00:36:53,878 --> 00:36:55,379
Come in!

556
00:37:08,192 --> 00:37:12,196
Yun. Chen. They're here…

557
00:37:12,830 --> 00:37:14,465
The Be-Bops.

558
00:37:17,635 --> 00:37:19,637
What do they want?

559
00:37:20,204 --> 00:37:21,172
Maybe see the movie?

560
00:37:31,582 --> 00:37:33,284
Oh, Mr. Trendy!

561
00:37:35,820 --> 00:37:38,055
Business is booming, I see.

562
00:37:38,956 --> 00:37:42,126
I was going to take my girl
to Maharaja in Roppongi,

563
00:37:42,793 --> 00:37:47,531
but I guess we have to see this first.

564
00:37:48,432 --> 00:37:52,803
Oh, hello.

565
00:37:52,870 --> 00:37:54,839
You're in the way! Move!

566
00:37:55,406 --> 00:37:57,375
Oh, no, the witch is here.

567
00:37:57,441 --> 00:37:58,776
Old lady Kuroe.

568
00:37:58,843 --> 00:38:01,279
How annoying,
right in the middle of the road!

569
00:38:02,046 --> 00:38:04,982
This is a public road, isn't it!

570
00:38:06,350 --> 00:38:07,485
Oh, Ms. Kuroe.

571
00:38:09,020 --> 00:38:10,655
You can watch, if you like.

572
00:38:12,723 --> 00:38:15,593
As if I would watch such trash!

573
00:38:16,494 --> 00:38:19,463
Everyone's brains
have rotted because of you!

574
00:38:20,765 --> 00:38:23,501
This country is heading toward ruin!

575
00:38:31,642 --> 00:38:34,178
Hey! What are you guys doing?

576
00:38:34,245 --> 00:38:36,414
This is the worst. It's Eto.

577
00:38:36,480 --> 00:38:38,749
Did you get permission from the school?

578
00:38:38,816 --> 00:38:41,786
- I haven't heard anything.
- We have permission from city hall.

579
00:38:41,852 --> 00:38:44,955
You have to apply with the school too!

580
00:38:45,556 --> 00:38:49,193
If you cause trouble for others,
it becomes the school's responsibility!

581
00:38:49,794 --> 00:38:51,128
I gave them permission.

582
00:38:53,564 --> 00:38:55,466
I have informed the principal as well.

583
00:39:01,672 --> 00:39:04,041
All right, let's watch. I'm excited.

584
00:39:04,709 --> 00:39:05,543
Let's go.

585
00:39:06,110 --> 00:39:07,611
<i>Sounds like you had fun.</i>

586
00:39:07,678 --> 00:39:09,814
<i>Probably thanks to our advising teacher.</i>

587
00:39:09,880 --> 00:39:11,816
<i>She was lovely.</i>

588
00:39:11,882 --> 00:39:13,951
We called her Matilda.

589
00:39:14,018 --> 00:39:15,052
Matilda?

590
00:39:15,119 --> 00:39:17,722
I liked Frau Bow.
I was in the Frau Bow camp.

591
00:39:17,788 --> 00:39:20,458
Man, Sayla is the only one for me.

592
00:39:20,524 --> 00:39:22,660
She's for kids.
I was into Hamon even back then.

593
00:39:22,727 --> 00:39:25,363
- Hamon was it for me.
- She's too mature!

594
00:39:25,930 --> 00:39:28,065
Stop, we're harassing her
with <i>Gundam </i>talk.

595
00:39:28,132 --> 00:39:30,434
I tried hard not to become
a weird <i>Gundam </i>old man.

596
00:39:31,135 --> 00:39:35,406
Well, anyway,
I got that she was a wonderful teacher.

597
00:39:37,575 --> 00:39:39,577
I wonder how she's doing?

598
00:39:39,643 --> 00:39:41,746
She quit suddenly and disappeared.

599
00:39:41,812 --> 00:39:44,648
Right, she was a sub,
so she was only there for a short while.

600
00:39:50,921 --> 00:39:53,557
- Is something wrong?
- Yeah.

601
00:39:53,624 --> 00:39:57,495
A strange memory just came back to me.

602
00:39:58,129 --> 00:39:59,296
A strange memory?

603
00:40:00,765 --> 00:40:02,133
I saw a UFO.

604
00:40:02,199 --> 00:40:04,201
- What?
- I saw it too.

605
00:40:04,268 --> 00:40:05,369
What?

606
00:40:05,936 --> 00:40:08,406
Didn't the three of us see it together?

607
00:40:08,472 --> 00:40:09,573
Yeah.

608
00:40:12,510 --> 00:40:16,180
<i>Ms. Matilda was pulled into the spaceship.</i>

609
00:40:17,548 --> 00:40:20,985
<i>And flown to another world.</i>

610
00:40:22,319 --> 00:40:24,989
Wait, is this from a movie or something?

611
00:40:25,055 --> 00:40:27,124
<i>Close Encounters, E.T.</i>

612
00:40:27,191 --> 00:40:29,360
Yasuko Sawaguchi
in <i>Princess from the Moon</i>.

613
00:40:30,361 --> 00:40:32,897
Ms. Matilda did look like
Yasuko Sawaguchi.

614
00:40:32,963 --> 00:40:36,434
We even saw Michael Jackson
at the Tokyo Dome with Matilda!

615
00:40:36,500 --> 00:40:40,104
- We did, someone gave us tickets.
- On the way back, we were moonwalking.

616
00:40:43,040 --> 00:40:45,509
They shot an episode
of <i>Oretachi Hyokinzoku </i>here.

617
00:40:45,576 --> 00:40:49,013
During the opening they would film locals
from where they were shooting.

618
00:40:49,079 --> 00:40:51,682
- It's a bird! It's a plane!
- It's Takecha--

619
00:40:51,749 --> 00:40:52,850
Never mind.

620
00:40:52,917 --> 00:40:56,320
Now, we're harassing her with 80s talk.

621
00:40:57,455 --> 00:41:02,059
It's interesting. Like I'm hearing stories
about another world.

622
00:41:02,126 --> 00:41:05,062
Another world, is that right? 1988.

623
00:41:05,129 --> 00:41:07,565
Looking back, it really is another world.

624
00:41:07,631 --> 00:41:12,002
In the middle of the bubble, everyone
was hyped up and bared their desires.

625
00:41:12,069 --> 00:41:16,240
<i>Can you fight for 24 hours?</i>

626
00:41:16,307 --> 00:41:18,709
- Right?
- You got it.

627
00:41:20,244 --> 00:41:22,179
Sounds like it was a good era.

628
00:41:22,246 --> 00:41:25,749
I don't know if it was good,
but it really was chaotic.

629
00:41:25,816 --> 00:41:27,751
The world wasn't just black and white.

630
00:41:27,818 --> 00:41:30,688
It was gray. That’s exactly why
the economy developed.

631
00:41:31,288 --> 00:41:34,859
Now that everything is cleaned up,
the energy is gone.

632
00:41:35,493 --> 00:41:39,163
We have to be mindful of those above us,
below us, and all around us.

633
00:41:39,230 --> 00:41:41,765
You have to make things
that won't offend anyone.

634
00:41:42,566 --> 00:41:45,569
Kurosawa, Coppola, and Kubrick
can't be born anymore.

635
00:41:45,636 --> 00:41:47,238
Same for your industry?

636
00:41:47,304 --> 00:41:50,107
Few domestic companies
can manage international events.

637
00:41:50,174 --> 00:41:51,509
Only we can do it.

638
00:41:51,575 --> 00:41:54,645
But if you do everything by the rules,
you can't move forward.

639
00:41:54,712 --> 00:41:58,148
The reason we work so desperately
isn't to line our own pockets.

640
00:41:58,215 --> 00:42:00,918
It's for Japan's sake!
Ordinary people don't understand that.

641
00:42:00,985 --> 00:42:03,654
People brandish simple justice,

642
00:42:03,721 --> 00:42:07,258
cater to the moods of the petty,
and it's ruining this country!

643
00:42:07,324 --> 00:42:08,192
Right, Kinpo?

644
00:42:09,159 --> 00:42:11,295
I am just a pretty ordinary person.

645
00:42:12,596 --> 00:42:15,866
- I wasn't talking about you.
- I am ordinary, compared to you two.

646
00:42:16,433 --> 00:42:19,436
I’ve not achieved my dreams
or been in the public spotlight.

647
00:42:19,503 --> 00:42:21,872
Never worked on national projects
for big companies.

648
00:42:22,473 --> 00:42:23,641
I run a barber shop,

649
00:42:24,341 --> 00:42:26,443
and I still live
with my mother, unmarried.

650
00:42:26,510 --> 00:42:27,578
That’s respectable.

651
00:42:27,645 --> 00:42:31,549
I'm sure you both came to see me
just to laugh at me.

652
00:42:32,483 --> 00:42:33,651
That’s not it at all.

653
00:42:34,251 --> 00:42:36,320
You came to feel a sense of superiority,

654
00:42:36,387 --> 00:42:38,656
to comfort yourself
that at least you're not me.

655
00:42:38,722 --> 00:42:40,858
- That's not it!
- It's fine.

656
00:42:42,226 --> 00:42:45,462
Even so, I’m happy you came to see me.

657
00:42:45,529 --> 00:42:46,463
Stop it, Kinpo.

658
00:42:47,097 --> 00:42:48,666
I would never look down on you.

659
00:42:49,967 --> 00:42:51,468
At least,

660
00:42:52,202 --> 00:42:53,304
I, myself,

661
00:42:53,871 --> 00:42:56,740
am a miserable person,
far from successful.

662
00:42:57,875 --> 00:42:58,876
But…

663
00:43:00,044 --> 00:43:01,445
I don't know about him.

664
00:43:02,880 --> 00:43:04,582
He’s a certified winner.

665
00:43:05,316 --> 00:43:07,518
Well, it's hard to say for sure, though.

666
00:43:08,352 --> 00:43:09,286
What did you say?

667
00:43:09,353 --> 00:43:11,722
You're looking down on us, aren't you?

668
00:43:12,423 --> 00:43:14,892
Even when we first met,
you looked down on us.

669
00:43:14,959 --> 00:43:16,927
You've always been like that!

670
00:43:27,104 --> 00:43:29,773
I bet you're hated by more people than me.

671
00:43:30,274 --> 00:43:33,143
You are correct. I'm good-for-nothing.

672
00:43:35,279 --> 00:43:38,148
We're making it awkward for Ms. Hakuba.

673
00:43:39,883 --> 00:43:41,218
It's wonderful, isn't it?

674
00:43:41,285 --> 00:43:45,322
A reunion with childhood friends
always ends up like this.

675
00:43:45,956 --> 00:43:48,559
Sorry to make you listen
to such ugly talk.

676
00:43:49,526 --> 00:43:50,427
Thanks for the drink.

677
00:43:51,195 --> 00:43:53,764
The sweet bean coffee was good. See you.

678
00:43:53,831 --> 00:43:56,300
Thank you very much. Please come again.

679
00:43:59,136 --> 00:44:01,538
That’s 1,390 yen.

680
00:44:01,605 --> 00:44:02,439
Let’s go home.

681
00:44:07,511 --> 00:44:10,381
Why don't we look into them a bit more?
Those bones…

682
00:44:11,281 --> 00:44:13,083
Bones? I think it's enough already.

683
00:44:13,150 --> 00:44:14,251
I'm curious.

684
00:44:14,318 --> 00:44:16,787
If we check each construction site,
we might find something.

685
00:44:16,854 --> 00:44:17,955
What will you do then?

686
00:44:18,922 --> 00:44:21,725
It was fun to see you two today.

687
00:44:21,792 --> 00:44:23,527
I feel refreshed after speaking my mind.

688
00:44:23,594 --> 00:44:25,329
Let's leave it there.

689
00:44:26,563 --> 00:44:30,334
Did Matilda look like Yasuko Sawaguchi?

690
00:44:31,368 --> 00:44:34,038
Did our movie ever get finished?

691
00:44:35,072 --> 00:44:37,875
We had a screening
at the community center.

692
00:44:37,941 --> 00:44:39,243
I remember it clearly too.

693
00:44:39,309 --> 00:44:41,311
That’s how I remember it too.

694
00:44:41,378 --> 00:44:43,380
Matilda watched it with us.
It was exciting.

695
00:44:44,548 --> 00:44:45,449
But…

696
00:44:46,684 --> 00:44:48,452
- But what?
- Ms. Hakuba.

697
00:44:50,287 --> 00:44:52,222
Let us see the break room.

698
00:44:52,289 --> 00:44:53,590
Hey, Kinpo! Hey.

699
00:44:57,394 --> 00:44:58,328
Certainly.

700
00:45:07,971 --> 00:45:08,972
Go ahead.

701
00:45:17,948 --> 00:45:20,918
There was a sign hanging here, right?
Matilda made it for us.

702
00:45:20,984 --> 00:45:22,553
Yes, there was.

703
00:45:24,455 --> 00:45:27,825
TANBE MIDDLE SCHOOL
MOVIE RESEARCH CLUB

704
00:45:39,570 --> 00:45:42,406
- All right, ready.
- Camera test, here we go.

705
00:45:45,442 --> 00:45:47,144
Ready, start!

706
00:45:57,621 --> 00:45:58,922
Good work, boys. Drinks?

707
00:45:58,989 --> 00:46:01,592
- We're filming!
- And, cut!

708
00:46:01,658 --> 00:46:04,561
I really don't like this. It's lame!

709
00:46:04,628 --> 00:46:06,130
- What do you mean?
- Calm down.

710
00:46:06,196 --> 00:46:08,065
Yoshii looks cool, right? Once more.

711
00:46:08,132 --> 00:46:10,534
I'm sure it will look cool
once we've tried it.

712
00:46:10,601 --> 00:46:13,103
All right, one more time.

713
00:46:16,373 --> 00:46:18,041
Ready, start!

714
00:46:36,760 --> 00:46:39,763
A little while ago,
while cleaning the house,

715
00:46:40,964 --> 00:46:42,065
I found this.

716
00:46:47,037 --> 00:46:50,007
She doesn't really look like
Yasuko Sawaguchi, does she?

717
00:46:51,875 --> 00:46:54,778
There was also this piece of paper.

718
00:46:54,845 --> 00:46:56,079
What was this again?

719
00:46:56,580 --> 00:46:58,048
HAVE YOU SEEN THIS PERSON?

720
00:46:58,115 --> 00:47:01,552
MISSING

721
00:47:04,454 --> 00:47:07,991
December 31, 1988.

722
00:47:09,159 --> 00:47:10,561
What happened?

723
00:47:13,330 --> 00:47:15,465
Even I was confused.

724
00:47:15,966 --> 00:47:18,802
When I saw the news about
the human bones found in Tanbe,

725
00:47:18,869 --> 00:47:23,073
for some reason I couldn't sit still,
and I felt like I had to let you know.

726
00:47:23,707 --> 00:47:25,809
I feel we have
to investigate it ourselves.

727
00:47:26,376 --> 00:47:28,779
Like it's our duty.

728
00:47:31,882 --> 00:47:32,783
Well…

729
00:47:36,553 --> 00:47:40,324
I liked my previous part-time job.

730
00:47:41,124 --> 00:47:43,493
It didn't require social skills.

731
00:47:45,429 --> 00:47:47,564
But it became hard to go on, so I quit.

732
00:47:48,532 --> 00:47:52,469
Someone told me not to report it,
but I reported it anyway.

733
00:47:56,874 --> 00:48:00,410
I’m the one who found the bones.

734
00:48:01,812 --> 00:48:02,813
- What?
- What?

735
00:48:27,771 --> 00:48:29,573
What are we doing?

736
00:48:34,645 --> 00:48:35,612
It’s just ahead.

737
00:48:39,483 --> 00:48:42,286
Yun, don't you recognize this area?

738
00:48:42,352 --> 00:48:43,854
What? No.

739
00:48:49,660 --> 00:48:50,594
What?

740
00:48:51,528 --> 00:48:53,130
Hey, what are you doing?

741
00:48:54,631 --> 00:48:58,302
- Hey!
- If we find more bones, then the police…

742
00:48:58,368 --> 00:48:59,770
Don't say such crazy things.

743
00:49:06,543 --> 00:49:07,511
Kinpo!

744
00:49:09,579 --> 00:49:10,547
Come here, Yun.

745
00:49:11,348 --> 00:49:14,084
I am on probation.

746
00:49:14,651 --> 00:49:15,719
There's a swamp ahead.

747
00:49:16,753 --> 00:49:18,322
I mean, a swamp used to be there.

748
00:49:19,790 --> 00:49:20,791
Swamp?

749
00:49:30,634 --> 00:49:34,104
Yun, did we see a UFO?

750
00:49:36,773 --> 00:49:38,775
What happened to Matilda?

751
00:49:45,048 --> 00:49:48,118
Memories can easily be misremembered.

752
00:49:48,185 --> 00:49:50,587
Especially for delusional
eighth-grader otakus.

753
00:49:54,224 --> 00:49:55,959
SCREENING CANCELLED

754
00:49:59,129 --> 00:50:01,098
- Come on over, Yun!
- Yun!

755
00:50:42,072 --> 00:50:43,440
What? Wait.

756
00:50:59,423 --> 00:51:00,891
It's over there.

757
00:51:29,719 --> 00:51:32,923
- Miss! Which do you think is better…
- Don't touch it!

758
00:51:32,989 --> 00:51:34,191
Miss?

759
00:51:34,858 --> 00:51:36,560
Your back.

760
00:51:46,770 --> 00:51:49,940
What did we rewrite?

761
00:51:50,006 --> 00:51:51,641
HATSUMODE

762
00:51:58,281 --> 00:52:02,385
What have we forgotten?

763
00:52:02,452 --> 00:52:03,920
Have you seen this person?

764
00:52:04,754 --> 00:52:06,223
Have you seen this person?

765
00:52:06,289 --> 00:52:08,258
Have you seen this woman? Please!

766
00:52:08,325 --> 00:52:11,728
She has been missing since New Year's Eve.
Please tell us all you know.

767
00:52:14,030 --> 00:52:14,898
Remember it!

768
00:52:17,868 --> 00:52:19,769
It's no use searching.

769
00:52:20,570 --> 00:52:22,672
The rumor is she was killed.

770
00:52:23,707 --> 00:52:26,643
They say she was sunk in the swamp.

771
00:52:34,251 --> 00:52:35,152
Remember.

772
00:52:36,920 --> 00:52:38,255
Remember!

773
00:53:40,850 --> 00:53:43,520
You should take a good look at this town.

774
00:53:44,020 --> 00:53:45,722
Everyone is being evicted, right?

775
00:53:45,789 --> 00:53:48,925
Miss, what will happen to you?

776
00:53:48,992 --> 00:53:52,696
You'll be here next term, right?
You'll teach us next year?

777
00:53:52,762 --> 00:53:55,131
I was just a temporary hire.

778
00:53:56,166 --> 00:53:58,101
I'll be gone before you know it.

779
00:53:58,868 --> 00:54:01,171
Where will you go after you quit school?

780
00:54:02,105 --> 00:54:04,040
Who knows?

781
00:54:04,941 --> 00:54:07,611
I’m not really cut out
to be a teacher anyway,

782
00:54:07,677 --> 00:54:09,546
so I'm going back to my own world.

783
00:54:09,613 --> 00:54:11,514
Where is that?

784
00:54:16,419 --> 00:54:18,421
Far beyond the moon.

785
00:54:19,489 --> 00:54:21,958
Nebula M78.

786
00:54:22,025 --> 00:54:24,761
Near Iscandar, maybe?

787
00:54:27,530 --> 00:54:30,100
Don't worry. It won't be sad.

788
00:54:32,335 --> 00:54:34,804
You’ll forget about me soon enough anyway.

789
00:54:43,980 --> 00:54:47,217
See you. Keep our promise.

790
00:55:00,497 --> 00:55:01,831
There's no doubt about it.

791
00:55:02,766 --> 00:55:05,268
The bones were Matilda's.

792
00:55:07,537 --> 00:55:10,440
Matilda was killed.

793
00:55:13,476 --> 00:55:15,178
It's our fault.

794
00:55:17,647 --> 00:55:21,484
<i>This is how I met the three old men.</i>

795
00:55:21,985 --> 00:55:22,952
Subtitle translation by: Quang N. N.
